<TITLE> HC halts mechanised excavation from Sylhet rivers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 14 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court has ordered a halt to mechanised excavation of rocks from beds of the rivers Piyain, Dauki and Dhala in Sylhet district. The bench of justice Syed Mahmud Hossain and Quamrul Islam Siddiqui issued the order on Thursday on a writ petition filed by Bangladesh Environmental Lawyers' Association (BELA) on August 29. Barrister Rokonuddin Mahmud and Dr Ali pleaded for the petitioner while deputy attorney general Razik Al Jalil stood for the state in the hearin
